# Laravel New Project Flow Reminder

When the user mentions creating a new Laravel project, moving a project into nested folders, or a Herd app not appearing, remind them of the full setup flow in this order:

```bash
cd "/path/to/project"
composer install
cp .env.example .env
php artisan key:generate
php artisan migrate
herd link
```

If the project is inside a deeper folder under a Herd parent directory, also suggest running:

```bash
cd "/path/to/parent-folder"
herd link
```

If frontend assets are missing, remind the user to run one of:
- `npm run dev`
- `npm run build`
- `composer run dev`
